            div.SpecialOffers
                h1 Special Offers
                .Picks
                    .itemPicks
                        div#BlueTrain.item
                            div.onHover
                            h1 Blue Train
                            p Luxury assumes a new dimension on The Blue Train which you will feel from the moment you step on board this newly re-furbished train, which is synonymous with luxury and hospitality.  Guests can expect personal and attentive service, a dedicated butler, sumptuous accommodation, sublime fine-dining and exquisite wines.
                            img(src="Images/BlueTrain.jpg")
                        div#CaribeanIslands.item
                            div.onHover
                            h1 French Coastal Break
                            p The southwestern seaside town of Biarritz provides a more laid back character than those on the Cote D’Azur, yet it still exudes charm and style. Resting on the French/Spanish border the town was often frequented by the Empress Eugenia de Montijo and her husband Napoleon III in the mid-19th century giving rise to its more glamorous status.
                            img(src="Images/Biarritz.jpg")
                            div.onHover
                        div#SanFrancisco.item
                            div.onHover
                            h1 Dubrovnik Summer Break
                            p Located on the Adriatic coast, Dubrovnik is a popular Mediterranean destination; a beautiful, sea port city with an illustrious past, where fortified walls of the Old Town trace their way to an enchanting coastline and orange tiled rooftops glow against a backdrop of deep blue sea.
                            img(src="Images/DubrovnikSummer.jpg")
                        div#LakeLouise.item
                            div.onHover
                            h1 LFrench Riviera Break
                            p Nice delights the visitor with its flower market, stunning coastline, beachfront bars and fabulous shopping. It is the unofficial capital of the Cote d’Azure, or as it is widely known, the French Riviera.
                            img(src="Images/Nice.jpg")
                        div#London.item
                            div.onHover
                            h1 Luxury Porto City Break
                            p Very much a waterside city, colourful Porto rises steeply from the River Douro which lies at its heart. Impressive bridges, including the Ponte Dona Maria designed by Gustave Eiffel, crisscross the water while traditional boats glide serenely beneath. Nearby the Atlantic Ocean beckons, where the upmarket suburb of Fos offers a seafront stroll between crashing surf and verdant palm trees.
                            img(src="Images/LuxuryPorto.jpg")
                        div#Singapore.item
                            div.onHover
                            h1 France Near Paris May
                            p Once discovered, never forgotten, the hidden charms of the Aisne Valley, with its gently flowing rivers and sleepy towns, is all the more enchanting because less than 90 minutes away lies the thrills of Disneyland Paris and the big-city sights of Paris itself!
                            img(src="Images/FranceNearParis.jpg")
